    "created_at": "2015-07-27T08:17:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-27T08:17:21Z",
    "body": "Reduce the code to `NativeImage.createFromPath`:\n\n```\nvar NativeImage = require('native-image');\n\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  for (var i = 0; i < 1000; ++i) {\n     var t = NativeImage.createFromPath('<path-image>.png');\n     t = null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nI can confirm that the destructor of [`NativeImage`](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/02bdace366f38271b5c186412f42810ecb06e99e/atom/common/api/atom_api_native_image.cc#L130) will be invoked for each instance when JS garbage collector running GC.  But the memory will not release even after the `NativeImage` destructor. Also appears on Windows.\n"
  },
