    "created_at": "2015-11-18T03:59:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-18T03:59:05Z",
    "body": "I'm still seeing a memory leak around `Tray.setImage()` on v0.33.2. Both of the following cause memory to stack up over time if called on a setInterval:\n`Tray.setImage(NativeImage.createFromPath(somePath));`\n`Tray.setImage(somePath);`\n\n I have a workaround where I make each of my NativeImages in memory up front and pass them to `setImage` when I need to.\n"
